This paper presents a hierarchical path planning framework that combines geometric path planning with reinforcement learning to plan rational paths for agents maneuvering in continuous and uncertain environments. The paper focuses on the application of this framework in robotics, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The use of reinforcement learning and policy iteration also suggests that this paper could fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with uncertainty and changes in the environment, which could place it under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses simulation experiments to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method, which could place it under the category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) if the simulations involve visual data.
